Especially if the OP lacks any military info themselves, then it just gets worse from there with stupid inflated deployments like "I am sending 2 million infantry, 25,000 tanks and 70,000 aircraft plus 5 million ships" with complete disregard for how much of a chore that would be to get every last man and bit of gear plus the vehicles themselves into the AO and get the whole operation rolling.

Note, while I see at most 10k infantry being somewhat manageable, that is still bordering on lunacy for me, personally. Plus falling back to http://www.broomdces.com/nseconomy/ for some mild idea of military management is quite useful, but it doesn't actively give a solid idea of reserves or military equipment. Sure, a nation may have 1 billion infantry, but for all we care about 99% of them are reserves with 1% being active duty, then from the reserves only 10% can be mobilized as a standing army.
